12/11/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Adrian Nastase said Thursday (11 November) that he would be a committed president. He pledged to head a team that would work closely with the government. His chief rival in the 28 November presidential vote, Bucharest Mayor Traian Basescu, has said Nastase cannot lead a team. 
In other news Thursday, Bucharest organised a regional exercise, simulating emergency responses to a natural disaster or other crisis. A similar drill will be conducted in 2006 under the auspices of NATO. (Rompres - 12/11/04; Rompres - 11/11/04) 
